        <div class="row"><div class="column text"><div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
  <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="Thu, 27 Jun 2024 02:03:56 +0000">
  <meta itemprop="dateModified" content="Thu, 27 Jun 2024 02:03:56 +0000">
  <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
    <meta itemprop="name" content="RICK RYCROFT and ROD McGUIRK, Associated Press, NewsNation">
  </span>
  <div class="card-content">
    <div class="image" role="presentation">
      <img src="/static8/world/2024/06/27/wikileaks-founder-julian-assange-returns-to-australia-after-us-legal-battle-ends.webp" alt="WikiLeaks founder Julian Assange returns to Australia a free man after US legal battle ends"
           itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
           referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">WikiLeaks founder Julian Assange returns to Australia a free man after US legal battle ends</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      CANBERRA, Australia (AP) — WikiLeaks founder Julian Assange returned to his homeland Australia aboard a charter jet and raised a celebratory clenched fist as his supporters cheered Wednesday after he pleaded guilty to obtaining and publishing U.S.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/world/2024/06/27/wikileaks-founder-julian-assange-returns-to-australia-after-us-legal-battle-ends/"  >(RICK RYCROFT and ROD McGUIRK, Associated Press, NewsNation)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div><div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
  <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="Fri, 28 Jun 2024 00:24:06 +0000">
  <meta itemprop="dateModified" content="Fri, 28 Jun 2024 00:24:06 +0000">
  <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
    <meta itemprop="name" content="JON GAMBRELL and NASSER KARIMI, Associated Press, KREX 5">
  </span>
  <div class="card-content">
    <div class="image" role="presentation">
      <img src="/static8/world/2024/06/28/first-candidate-drops-out-of-iran-presidential-election-due-to-take-place-friday-amid-voter-apathy.webp" alt="Two candidates drop out of Iran presidential election, due to take place Friday amid voter apathy"
           itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
           referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">Two candidates drop out of Iran presidential election, due to take place Friday amid voter apathy</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      DUBAI, United Arab Emirates (AP) — Two candidates in Iran's presidential election withdrew from the race as the country on Thursday prepared for the upcoming vote, an effort by hard-liners to coalesce around a unity candidate in the polls to replace the late President Ebrahim Raisi.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/world/2024/06/28/first-candidate-drops-out-of-iran-presidential-election-due-to-take-place-friday-amid-voter-apathy/"  >(JON GAMBRELL and NASSER KARIMI, Associated Press, KREX 5)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div><div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
  <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="Tue, 25 Jun 2024 18:49:49 +0000">
  <meta itemprop="dateModified" content="Tue, 25 Jun 2024 18:49:49 +0000">
  <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
    <meta itemprop="name" content="Anna Kutz, WFLA, NBC">
